</code></div></div></pre><p>Please note the following:</p><ul><li>The <code>$uploadDir</code> variable should be set to the path of the directory where you want to store the images.</li><li><code>move_uploaded_file</code> function is used to securely move the uploaded file to the destination directory.</li><li>You must ensure that the directory has the correct permissions to allow the PHP script to write to it.</li><li>The SQL INSERT statement now should include a <code>person_image_path</code> column instead of <code>person_image</code> which will store the path to the image file instead of the image data itself. You'll need to create this column in your <code>people_team_startups</code> table if it doesn't already exist.</li></ul><h3>Modify Your Database Table</h3><p>Change the <code>person_image</code> BLOB column to a <code>VARCHAR</code> to store the file path:</p><pre><div class="dark bg-gray-950 rounded-md"><div class="flex items-center relative text-token-text-secondary bg-token-main-surface-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between rounded-t-md"><span>sql</span><span class="" data-state="closed"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="icon-sm"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M12 4C10.8954 4 10 4.89543 10 6H14C14 4.89543 13.1046 4 12 4ZM8.53513 4C9.22675 2.8044 10.5194 2 12 2C13.4806 2 14.7733 2.8044 15.4649 4H17C18.6569 4 20 5.34315 20 7V19C20 20.6569 18.6569 22 17 22H7C5.34315 22 4 20.6569 4 19V7C4 5.34315 5.34315 4 7 4H8.53513ZM8 6H7C6.44772 6 6 6.44772 6 7V19C6 19.5523 6.44772 20 7 20H17C17.5523 20 18 19.5523 18 19V7C18 6.44772 17.5523 6 17 6H16C16 7.10457 15.1046 8 14 8H10C8.89543 8 8 7.10457 8 6Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg>Copy code</button></span></div><div class="p-4 overflow-y-auto"><code class="!whitespace-pre hljs language-sql"><span class="hljs-keyword">ALTER</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">TABLE</span> people_team_startups RENAME <span class="hljs-keyword">TO</span> old_table;

<span class="hljs-keyword">CREATE</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">TABLE</span> people_team_startups (
  id <span class="hljs-type">INTEGER</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">PRIMARY</span> KEY,
  startup_id <span class="hljs-type">INTEGER</span>,
  Name TEXT,
