065 10.2616 14.2466 10.4877 14.2479 10.7175L14.2424 21.9419ZM16.071 17.9991L20.4018 15.4978L24.7325 17.9975V22.9985L20.4018 25.4983L16.071 22.9985V17.9991Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></div></div></div></div></div><div class="relative flex w-full flex-col agent-turn"><div class="font-semibold select-none">ChatGPT</div><div class="flex-col gap-1 md:gap-3"><div class="flex flex-grow flex-col max-w-full"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="f30a9106-9ae3-457c-bce7-e77f31503579" class="min-h-[20px] text-message flex flex-col items-start gap-3 whitespace-pre-wrap break-words [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-5 overflow-x-auto"><div class="markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert dark"><p>To alter your <code>startups_information</code> table to change the <code>logo</code> column from a BLOB to a TEXT type, you will need to follow a similar process as before. This will involve creating a new table with the updated column type, copying the data over (excluding the BLOB data), and then dropping the old table.</p><p>Here is how you can do it in SQLite:</p><pre><div class="dark bg-gray-950 rounded-md"><div class="flex items-center relative text-token-text-secondary bg-token-main-surface-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between rounded-t-md"><span>sql</span><span class="" data-state="closed"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="icon-sm"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M12 4C10.8954 4 10 4.89543 10 6H14C14 4.89543 13.1046 4 12 4ZM8.53513 4C9.22675 2.8044 10.5194 2 12 2C13.4806 2 14.7733 2.8044 15.4649 4H17C18.6569 4 20 5.34315 20 7V19C20 20.6569 18.6569 22 17 22H7C5.34315 22 4 20.6569 4 19V7C4 5.34315 5.34315 4 7 4H8.53513ZM8 6H7C6.44772 6 6 6.44772 6 7V19C6 19.5523 6.44772 20 7 20H17C17.5523 20 18 19.5523 18 19V7C18 6.44772 17.5523 6 17 6H16C16 7.10457 15.1046 8 14 8H10C8.89543 8 8 7.10457 8 6Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg>Copy code</button></span></div><div class="p-4 overflow-y-auto"><code class="!whitespace-pre hljs language-sql"><span class="hljs-comment">-- Rename the old table</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">ALTER</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">TABLE</span> startups_information RENAME <span class="hljs-keyword">TO</span> old_startups_info;

<span class="hljs-comment">-- Create a new table with the `logo` column as TEXT</span>
<span class="hljs-keyword">CREATE</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">TABLE</span> startups_information (
  startup_id <span class="hljs-type">INTEGER</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">PRIMARY</span> KEY,
  startup_name TEXT,
  industry TEXT,
  location TEXT,
  vision TEXT,
  usp TEXT,
  motivation TEXT,
  target_market TEXT,
  customer_num <span class="hljs-type">INTEGER</span>,
  revenue_till_date <span class="hljs-type">INTEGER</span>,
  Team_size <span class="hljs-type">INTEGER</span>,
  Founding_year <span class="hljs-type">INTEGER</span>,
  logo TEXT, <span class="hljs-comment">-- Now a TEXT type</span>
  Funding_stage TEXT,
  Customer_acc_cost <span class="hljs-type">INTEGER</span>,
  Retention_rate_perc <span class="hljs-type">INTEGER</span>,
  User_growth_perc <span class="hljs-type">INTEGER</span>,
  <span class="hljs-keyword">FOREIGN</span> KEY (startup_id) <span class="hljs-keyword">REFERENCES</span> login(id)
);

<span class="hljs-comment">-- Copy the data from the old table to the new table</span>
