```php
$stmt = $pdo-&gt;prepare("SELECT ii.*, l.Name FROM information_investor ii INNER JOIN login l ON ii.investor_id = l.id WHERE ii.investor_id &gt; :lastId ORDER BY ii.investor_id ASC LIMIT 1");
$stmt-&gt;execute(['lastId' =&gt; $lastId]);
$newContent = $stmt-&gt;fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);
```

This query joins the `information_investor` table (aliased as `ii`) with the `login` table (aliased as `l`) on their respective `investor_id` and `id` fields. It selects all columns from `information_investor` and the `Name` column from the `login` table for the next investor based on the passed `lastId`. The result will include the investor's name as part of the `$newContent` array, which you can then use in your dynamic content generation:

